nicotine wasn"t addictive. In fact, he said it is. Contrary to polupar myth that it is just a bad habit. It is only addictive for three days though. And the withdrawal pangs feel just like hunger, but since they aren"t hunger, food doesn"t relieve them, so don"t eat when you have them and you won"t gain weight. They only last a few seconds. Once you get past those three days without a smoke, the rest is purely psychological, not addiction.
